Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • domain.User

  • public final class User
extends java.lang.Object
    Class Description: User class that defines which attributes every type of user has.
    Author:
    Tristen Kreutz, Cesar Guzman, Jesse Goerzen

    • Field Detail

      • email

        private java.lang.String email
        The email address of the user. This is unique to each user. Must be less than or equal to 100 characters.

      • active

        private boolean active
        Whether the user is active in the system.

      • permissionLevel

        private int permissionLevel
        The level of permission the user has in the system. Valid values are given by the constants DEFAULT, USER, TAX_PREPARER, ADMIN, and SYSADMIN.

      • title

        private java.lang.String title
        The title by which the user wants to be addressed. Must be one of Na for not applicable, Mr for mister, Mrs for missus, Ms for miss, or Mx.

      • fName

        private java.lang.String fName
        The user's first name. Must be 25 characters or less.

      • mName

        private java.lang.String mName
        The user's middle name. Must be 25 characters or less.

      • lName

        private java.lang.String lName
        The user's last name. Must be 25 characters or less.

      • passHash

        private java.lang.String passHash
        The hashed form of the user's password. Is based on the user's salt, as well as the password only known by them. Is 64 characters long.

      • passSalt

        private java.lang.String passSalt
        The random string of characters used as a salt for hashing the user's password. Is 44 characters long.

      • creationDate

        private java.util.Date creationDate
        The day and time that the user was created.

      • phone

        private java.lang.String phone
        The user's phone number. Must be 15 characters or less. TODO Must follow ....

      • fax

        private java.lang.String fax
        The user's fax number. Must be 15 characters or less.

      • streetAddress

        private java.lang.String streetAddress
        The first line of the user's mailing street address. Must be 320 characters or fewer.

      • streetAddress2

        private java.lang.String streetAddress2
        The second line of the user's mailing street address. Must be 320 characters or fewer.

      • city

        private java.lang.String city
        The city of the user's mailing address. Must be 100 characters or fewer.

      • province

        private java.lang.String province
        The province of the user's mailing address. Must follow the 2 character format of the ISO_3166-2 standard.

      • country

        private java.lang.String country
        The country of the user's mailing address. Must follow the 2 character format of the ISO_3166-2 standard.

      • postalCode

        private java.lang.String postalCode
        The postal code of the user's mailing address. Must be 10 characters long or fewer.

      • language

        private java.lang.String language
        The user's preferred language. Must be either en for English, or es for Espa�ol.

      • verified

        private boolean verified
        Whether or not the user's email address has been verified.

      • verificationID

        private java.lang.String verificationID
        The String containing the UUID used to identify this user for verification attempts through email.

      • lastVerificationAttempt

        private java.util.Date lastVerificationAttempt
        The time and date that the user last requested an action that required verification.

      • lastVerificationType

        private int lastVerificationType
        The last type of request the user gave for something that required verification.
